242
00:11:12,296 --> 00:11:13,464
[chuckles softly]

243
00:11:13,547 --> 00:11:15,466
Now if you don't want to play,
you don't have to.

244
00:11:15,549 --> 00:11:16,967
I am happy to take you home--

245
00:11:17,051 --> 00:11:18,469
No, I'm okay.

246
00:11:18,552 --> 00:11:20,179
[inhales deeply] I want to.

247
00:11:20,262 --> 00:11:21,806
[breathes deeply]

248
00:11:21,889 --> 00:11:23,641
Thank you so much, Rhyah.

249
00:11:24,266 --> 00:11:25,101
Bring it in.

250
00:11:28,604 --> 00:11:30,606
[orchestra warming up]

251
00:11:39,490 --> 00:11:41,742
[orchestra playing classical music]

252
00:11:41,826 --> 00:11:45,162
[McEnroe] Devi overcame
her orchestra-centric PTSD

253
00:11:45,246 --> 00:11:48,833
with the help of, let's be honest,
basically her mother-in-law.

254
00:11:49,417 --> 00:11:51,335
As she played the shit out of Liszt,

255
00:11:51,419 --> 00:11:53,921
she felt like nothing
could bring her down.

256
00:12:02,972 --> 00:12:04,974
[indistinct chatter]

257
00:12:06,350 --> 00:12:08,894
Okay, before Nalini comes out with Devi,
we need to talk.

258
00:12:08,978 --> 00:12:11,772
-I'm not sure about you two dating.
-[Des] What? Why?

259
00:12:11,856 --> 00:12:14,442
Because, honey,
I don't think Devi is right for you.

260
00:12:14,525 --> 00:12:17,987
Don't get me wrong,
she's a wonderful girl, but… [sighs]

261
00:12:18,070 --> 00:12:21,323
…earlier tonight, I found her
on the bathroom floor hysterical.

262
00:12:21,407 --> 00:12:24,493
She said she saw
her dead father in the audience.

263
00:12:24,577 --> 00:12:25,995
[Des] Oh my God. Is she okay?

264
00:12:26,078 --> 00:12:30,249
She's fine. But, honey,
that girl has a lot of problems.

265
00:12:31,167 --> 00:12:32,001
[woman] Excuse me.

266
00:12:33,127 --> 00:12:33,961
Sorry, ma'am.

267
00:12:34,044 --> 00:12:35,838
You're overreacting. It's fine.

268
00:12:35,921 --> 00:12:38,716
It's not fine. You are too young
to have to deal with all of that.

269
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:42,178
I want you to end things,
and I'm not gonna change my mind.

270
00:12:48,184 --> 00:12:49,435
Hi. [gasps]

271
00:12:49,518 --> 00:12:51,520
You were absolutely amazing.

272
00:12:51,604 --> 00:12:55,149
Thank you, Rhyah.
And thanks for earlier too.

273
00:12:55,232 --> 00:12:56,233
[chuckles]

274
00:12:56,317 --> 00:12:59,653
So should we go somewhere for dessert?
Harpist's treat.

275
00:12:59,737 --> 00:13:01,906
Or actually, harpist's mom's treat.

276
00:13:01,989 --> 00:13:05,409
[laughs] Yes, fine.
It would be my pleasure.

277
00:13:05,493 --> 00:13:08,788
Oh, I wish,
but we should really head home.

278
00:13:08,871 --> 00:13:10,873
Thank you, though,
for such a wonderful night.

279
00:13:10,956 --> 00:13:12,958
-[Nalini] Meet you in the car, kanna.
-[Devi] Yeah.

280
00:13:13,834 --> 00:13:16,629
-So, see you tomorrow for bowling?
-[hesitating]

281
00:13:17,213 --> 00:13:20,841
Actually, I just remembered
I have a huge paper due on Monday.

282
00:13:20,925 --> 00:13:22,426
So I… I need the weekend.

283
00:13:23,469 --> 00:13:24,887
That's cool. How's next week?

284
00:13:26,263 --> 00:13:27,556
-Sure.
-[chuckles]

285
00:13:28,224 --> 00:13:30,851
-You really were great.
-Mmm.

286
00:13:37,066 --> 00:13:38,275
[sighs]

287
00:13:38,359 --> 00:13:39,693
[school bell ringing]

288
00:13:39,777 --> 00:13:42,029
[McEnroe] The concert
had been a wild success.

289
00:13:42,112 --> 00:13:45,491
Devi faced her trauma,
her mom was happily Team Des,

290
00:13:45,574 --> 00:13:47,618
and she spanked her harp solo.

291
00:13:47,701 --> 00:13:51,664
So it must be in her head that Des
had felt a little distant all week.

292
00:13:51,747 --> 00:13:54,917
[Devi] Hey, it's been a minute.
Wanna hang this weekend?

293
00:13:56,168 --> 00:13:57,419
[Des] You know what?

294
00:13:57,503 --> 00:14:00,464
I forgot to tell you I'm going to Stanford
this weekend to scope out housing.

295
00:14:00,548 --> 00:14:01,799
Text you when I get back.

296
00:14:03,133 --> 00:14:04,760
Hey, David, do you have a minute?

297
00:14:05,344 --> 00:14:07,137
I only need 30 seconds.

298
00:14:07,221 --> 00:14:09,557
Sweatshirt's crazy,
pants too small, babyGap shoes.

299
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:11,016
[chuckles] Great, sick burns.

300
00:14:11,100 --> 00:14:13,602
Listen, I actually need to talk to you
about something serious.

301
00:14:18,524 --> 00:14:21,735
At the concert, I overheard Des's mom
tell him that he has to break up with you.

302
00:14:22,403 --> 00:14:24,655
What? That's impossible. Rhyah loves me.

303
00:14:24,738 --> 00:14:27,950
She said you have a lot of problems
and that he needed to end it.

304
00:14:28,450 --> 00:14:29,368
I'm really sorry.

305
00:14:30,411 --> 00:14:31,370
[sighs]

306
00:14:32,037 --> 00:14:35,875
Well, then I guess you misunderstood
because Des didn't break up with me.

307
00:14:35,958 --> 00:14:38,419
So, he's been totally normal since then?

308
00:14:38,502 --> 00:14:41,922
Well, actually, I haven't seen him,
but that's only because he's busy.

309
00:14:42,006 --> 00:14:45,050
-Right. He's pulling a slow fade.
-It's not a slow fade.

310
00:14:45,134 --> 00:14:47,469
Right. Right, right.
He's just fading away very slowly.

311
00:14:47,553 --> 00:14:48,762
You know what, Ben?

312
00:14:48,846 --> 00:14:51,140
You've been throwing digs
at Des since you met him.

313
00:14:51,223 --> 00:14:53,392
You're just jealous
because you're lonely, and miserable,

314
00:14:53,475 --> 00:14:55,561
and you want everyone else
to be as unhappy as you are.

315
00:14:55,644 --> 00:14:58,439
So, guess what?
Here's a quick fade. Buh-bye!

316
00:15:05,404 --> 00:15:08,449
Hey there, buddy.
Haven't heard from you all week.

317
00:15:08,532 --> 00:15:09,366
How you doin'?

318
00:15:12,161 --> 00:15:14,496
I know it's a shock about Paxton.

319
00:15:14,580 --> 00:15:16,916
I can tell you're upset
by your stress carving.

320
00:15:16,999 --> 00:15:18,459
I'm not upset. [scoffs]

321
00:15:18,542 --> 00:15:21,253
I always carve a tombstone
with Traxton written on it.

322
00:15:21,337 --> 00:15:24,089
Trent, I'm your girlfriend.

323
00:15:24,173 --> 00:15:25,049
Talk to me.

324
00:15:25,716 --> 00:15:28,636
I just don't understand
why everyone always has to leave.

325
00:15:28,719 --> 00:15:30,262
First, my dad goes to Napa,

326
00:15:30,346 --> 00:15:33,641
and then my pet rat goes to the rat trap
that my mom set, and now Paxton?

327
00:15:33,724 --> 00:15:36,518
But you and Paxton will always be friends.

328
00:15:36,602 --> 00:15:38,479
You have to let him go.

329
00:15:38,562 --> 00:15:40,648
Good friends don't hold each other back.

330
00:15:40,731 --> 00:15:42,399
Oh, so you're on his side.

331
00:15:42,483 --> 00:15:44,568
Great. Why don't you go to Arizona too?

332
00:15:44,652 --> 00:15:46,820
Enjoy not having daylight savings time.

333
00:15:46,904 --> 00:15:49,907
You know what, Trent? Grow up!

334
00:15:49,990 --> 00:15:52,242
Something great happened
to your best friend,

335
00:15:52,326 --> 00:15:53,827
and you're being selfish.

336
00:15:53,911 --> 00:15:59,333
And frankly, this energy is very unsexy
to me, and I'm walking away now.

337
00:16:02,544 --> 00:16:06,090
[McEnroe] The next day, Ben's voice
was still buzzing in Devi's ear.

338
00:16:06,173 --> 00:16:08,717
Ben's full of shit.
Right? Des is just busy.

339
00:16:08,801 --> 00:16:11,470
He's literally up in Stanford right now
making sure he doesn't end up

340
00:16:11,553 --> 00:16:12,846
in the dry dorm with the Mormons.

341
00:16:12,930 --> 00:16:15,599
Yeah. Forget Ben. You and Des are perfect.

342
00:16:15,683 --> 00:16:17,559
He's probably up in Palo Alto

343
00:16:17,643 --> 00:16:20,646
bragging about his hot girlfriend
to the residence hall staff.

344
00:16:20,729 --> 00:16:23,732
-Yeah.
-I think he's getting coffee on Ventura.

345
00:16:23,816 --> 00:16:25,818
-What?
-Okay, so…

346
00:16:26,318 --> 00:16:28,278
I so happened to stumble
upon Addison's Insta,

347
00:16:28,362 --> 00:16:29,947
not that I look at it a lot or anything,

348
00:16:30,030 --> 00:16:32,116
but they just went live from Dark Roast,

349
00:16:32,199 --> 00:16:34,785
and you can see Des
in the reflection of their sunglasses.

350
00:16:37,371 --> 00:16:38,622
What the hell?

351
00:16:40,749 --> 00:16:44,253
Hey! How's Stanford going? Send a pic!

352
00:16:46,964 --> 00:16:49,383
[Des] It's beautiful here!
I love the architecture.

353
00:16:49,466 --> 00:16:52,261
Oh my God, what an asshole.
We have to confront him!

354
00:16:52,344 --> 00:16:55,014
I wish I could,
but if I miss my costume fitting,

355
00:16:55,097 --> 00:16:58,517
Jonah will dress me
in gasoline-soaked rags. His words.

356
00:16:58,600 --> 00:17:01,937
I'll come with you,
and not just because Addison's there,

357
00:17:02,021 --> 00:17:03,063
because I'm a good friend.

358
00:17:04,898 --> 00:17:06,900
[indistinct chatter]

359
00:17:09,611 --> 00:17:13,032
Well, well, well. I heard that Stanford
had a sprawling campus,

360
00:17:13,115 --> 00:17:16,410
but I didn't realize that it reached
all the way down to Southern California!

361
00:17:16,493 --> 00:17:17,536
Devi, I can explain.

362
00:17:17,619 --> 00:17:20,789
Explain what? That you and your mom
decided to break up with me,

363
00:17:20,873 --> 00:17:22,291
but you didn't want to let me know?

364
00:17:22,374 --> 00:17:25,335
Yeah, you had a pretty
public conversation at my school,

365
00:17:25,419 --> 00:17:27,212
and I got eyes everywhere.

366
00:17:27,296 --> 00:17:29,923
Devi, I'm sorry I lied to you. I…

367
00:17:30,466 --> 00:17:33,260
I just didn't know what to do. I mean,
I really don't want to break up--

368
00:17:33,343 --> 00:17:35,804
-Then don't!
-I can't go against her. She's my mom!

369
00:17:35,888 --> 00:17:38,849
I go against my mom,
like, 40 times a day. It's fine.

370
00:17:38,932 --> 00:17:41,935
[sighs] Look, Devi, you're cool and all,

371
00:17:42,561 --> 00:17:45,022
but, like, dating you
isn't worth pissing off my mom.

372
00:17:46,315 --> 00:17:48,776
-I mean, she still pays for my phone.
-[scoffs]

373
00:17:51,612 --> 00:17:52,738
[Fabiola gasps]

374
00:17:55,157 --> 00:17:56,033
Devi!

375
00:17:57,201 --> 00:17:58,952
Devi Vishwakumar, come with me.

376
00:17:59,036 --> 00:18:01,038
-[scoffs]
-[people murmuring]

377
00:18:03,457 --> 00:18:05,417
-[Rhyah] Come on.
-See ya.

378
00:18:06,835 --> 00:18:07,961
[exhales]

379
00:18:09,213 --> 00:18:10,464
Seat taken?

380
00:18:20,974 --> 00:18:22,643
Hey, bro, what's up?

381
00:18:23,477 --> 00:18:24,311
Nothing.

382
00:18:24,812 --> 00:18:28,065
Okay. Anything you want to talk about?

383
00:18:28,148 --> 00:18:29,483
[sighs]

384
00:18:29,566 --> 00:18:34,238
I just wanted to say that I'm cool
with you going to Arizona

385
00:18:34,321 --> 00:18:35,364
on one condition.

386
00:18:36,031 --> 00:18:36,865
What's that?

387
00:18:36,949 --> 00:18:38,992
[voice breaking] You're not allowed
to make a new…

388
00:18:39,076 --> 00:18:41,620
[clears throat] …best friend there.

389
00:18:41,703 --> 00:18:43,455
[scoffs] Dude…

390
00:18:48,502 --> 00:18:51,588
Never. No one can take your place, bro.

391
00:18:51,672 --> 00:18:53,006
You're my number one boy.

392
00:18:53,090 --> 00:18:55,050
[sighs] Bring it in, my sweet prince.

393
00:18:56,260 --> 00:18:57,302
Yeah!

394
00:18:57,803 --> 00:19:00,514
Guess I'll need some Mentos
to remember you by.

395
00:19:01,140 --> 00:19:03,517
-I think you mean mementos.
-[Trent gasps] Oh!

396
00:19:04,434 --> 00:19:05,310
[gasps]

397
00:19:05,936 --> 00:19:07,980
That's my warming jacket for swimming.

398
00:19:08,063 --> 00:19:09,815
Signature Paxton. [chuckles]

399
00:19:09,898 --> 00:19:10,941
Looks good.

400
00:19:11,024 --> 00:19:13,068
Oh, sick!

401
00:19:13,152 --> 00:19:14,570
-I'll take these too.
-Okay.

402
00:19:14,653 --> 00:19:17,573
Oh, I suppose I should leave you
with something of mine.

403
00:19:17,656 --> 00:19:20,409
No, you don't have to do that, man.
It's fine--

404
00:19:24,496 --> 00:19:25,497
[Paxton chuckles]

405
00:19:25,581 --> 00:19:27,332
-[chuckles]
-[Paxton] Thanks, man.

406
00:19:27,416 --> 00:19:29,918
Look, you know I'll come back
to visit a lot, right?

407
00:19:30,002 --> 00:19:31,378
You and I will always be friends.

408
00:19:31,461 --> 00:19:34,506
Yeah, Eleanor said the same thing.

409
00:19:34,590 --> 00:19:36,800
She's really dope. Don't mess that up.

410
00:19:43,223 --> 00:19:46,185
Hi, Nal.
We have a little bit of a situation.

411
00:19:46,685 --> 00:19:50,647
I just witnessed Devi throw coffee
directly into my son's face.

412
00:19:50,731 --> 00:19:52,107
Uh, it was iced coffee.

413
00:19:52,191 --> 00:19:56,403
Still, I think it's best we pump
the brakes on this relationship.

414
00:19:56,486 --> 00:19:58,071
As much as I love Devi--

415
00:19:58,155 --> 00:20:00,115
You don't love me.

416
00:20:00,199 --> 00:20:01,575
I heard what you said.

417
00:20:02,075 --> 00:20:05,787
She told Des to break up with me
because I "had a lot of problems."

418
00:20:05,871 --> 00:20:06,872
You did?

419
00:20:06,955 --> 00:20:09,499
-I never said that, all I said--
-[Des] Mom.

420
00:20:10,292 --> 00:20:11,126
Just admit it.

421
00:20:12,085 --> 00:20:13,045
[sighs]

422
00:20:13,128 --> 00:20:16,089
Okay. Yes, I suggested
that Des end things,

423
00:20:16,173 --> 00:20:19,509
but I was just thinking
of what's best for both of our kids.

424
00:20:19,593 --> 00:20:23,347
Do you really think Devi
is a danger to your son?

425
00:20:23,430 --> 00:20:25,307
Well, she did throw coffee in his face.

426
00:20:25,390 --> 00:20:26,683
Iced coffee.

427
00:20:26,767 --> 00:20:29,811
Look, Nal, I appreciate
what you and Devi have been through,

428
00:20:29,895 --> 00:20:32,397
but you said it yourself,
his future is so bright.

429
00:20:33,106 --> 00:20:34,942
I don't want anything
to get in the way of that.

430
00:20:35,025 --> 00:20:36,318
[Nalini] Rhyah,

431
00:20:36,401 --> 00:20:39,947
how dare you come to my house
and talk about my daughter this way?

432
00:20:40,948 --> 00:20:42,991
Devi does not have problems.

433
00:20:43,075 --> 00:20:45,535
She's just been through
something unimaginable

434
00:20:45,619 --> 00:20:50,207
that would break someone as flimsy as you
in an instant, and she has persevered.

435
00:20:50,290 --> 00:20:53,043
How can you talk to me like that, Nalini?

436
00:20:53,126 --> 00:20:55,629
I mean, I have been
such a great friend to you.

437
00:20:55,712 --> 00:20:57,547
You don't think of me as a friend.

438
00:20:57,631 --> 00:21:01,385
You think of me as a project
that you can, uh, feed seeds to.

439
00:21:01,468 --> 00:21:02,761
Fine. If that's how you feel,

440
00:21:02,844 --> 00:21:05,764
then I guess I'll take someone else
to Jessica Alba's baby food tasting.

441
00:21:06,348 --> 00:21:08,976
Fantastic. Now, if you'll excuse me,

442
00:21:09,059 --> 00:21:12,354
I need to eat a bag
of heavily processed Bugle chips.

443
00:21:13,313 --> 00:21:14,147
Wow!

444
00:21:19,987 --> 00:21:21,154
I really am sorry.

445
00:21:22,572 --> 00:21:23,407
Me too.

446
00:21:33,792 --> 00:21:34,960
[knocking on door]

447
00:21:35,460 --> 00:21:37,462
[sentimental song playing softly]

448
00:21:39,673 --> 00:21:43,135
[sighs] Devi, you okay?

449
00:21:47,347 --> 00:21:48,307
Mm-hmm.

450
00:21:49,182 --> 00:21:51,393
Thanks for ripping Rhyah a new one.

451
00:21:51,476 --> 00:21:52,644
She deserved it.

452
00:21:52,728 --> 00:21:53,895
[inhales deeply]

453
00:21:53,979 --> 00:21:58,108
Listen, I'm really sorry about Des.
I know you were excited about that.

454
00:21:58,191 --> 00:21:59,359
-Yeah.
-[Nalini] Mm-hmm.

455
00:21:59,443 --> 00:22:00,652
[inhales deeply]

456
00:22:00,736 --> 00:22:04,531
I actually thought for a second that
I was gonna be able to live a normal life,

457
00:22:04,614 --> 00:22:06,908
but I guess I'm too much
of a freak for that.

458
00:22:06,992 --> 00:22:09,703
You're not a freak.
Don't listen to a word of what Rhyah said.

459
00:22:09,786 --> 00:22:12,789
Mom, she's not completely wrong, you know.

460
00:22:13,415 --> 00:22:15,125
I am kind of a lot.

461
00:22:16,501 --> 00:22:17,794
Before the concert…

462
00:22:17,878 --> 00:22:19,046
[inhales deeply]

463
00:22:19,129 --> 00:22:21,256
…I thought I saw Dad in the audience.

464
00:22:23,717 --> 00:22:26,303
That's okay. I see him everywhere.

465
00:22:26,970 --> 00:22:30,515
Once I thought I saw him cut me off
in traffic, and I followed that man home.

466
00:22:30,599 --> 00:22:32,059
[chuckles] Damn.

467
00:22:32,142 --> 00:22:33,602
[both chuckle]

468
00:22:34,519 --> 00:22:35,437
Um…

469
00:22:41,651 --> 00:22:43,320
What if, um…

470
00:22:44,363 --> 00:22:48,408
What if nobody ever loves me
because I'm always too much?

471
00:22:48,492 --> 00:22:50,452
[chuckles] Oh, Devi.

472
00:22:51,953 --> 00:22:53,538
[sighs] Listen to me.

473
00:22:54,956 --> 00:22:57,626
You're never too much,
and you're always enough.

474
00:22:59,628 --> 00:23:03,090
And one day, you will find someone
who loves you exactly as you are,

475
00:23:03,590 --> 00:23:04,674
just like I do.

476
00:23:04,758 --> 00:23:05,675
[sniffles]

477
00:23:09,721 --> 00:23:10,680
[sniffles]

478
00:23:10,764 --> 00:23:12,057
I love you too, Mom.

479
00:23:15,477 --> 00:23:18,146
Now, come downstairs,

480
00:23:18,230 --> 00:23:21,691
and we can watch our Property Brothers
install a waterfall island.

481
00:23:22,401 --> 00:23:23,610
[chuckles]

482
00:23:24,277 --> 00:23:25,195
Okay.

483
00:23:32,244 --> 00:23:34,246
[pop rock music playing]

484
00:23:42,170 --> 00:23:45,507
[sighs] So, has your back
always been shaped this way?

485
